{"parse":{"title":"Easiteach","pageid":23412777,"revid":754215575,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Easiteach</b> is a suite of <a href=\"/wiki/Software\" title=\"Software\">software</a> programs mainly used in conjunction with <a href=\"/wiki/Interactive_whiteboard\" title=\"Interactive whiteboard\">interactive whiteboards</a> in schools.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The software is made by <a href=\"/wiki/RM_plc\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"RM plc\">Research Machines Ltd</a>, who provide ICT software and services to schools worldwide. The major advantage of Easiteach is that it will work with most popular brands of whiteboard, whereas many other popular packages will only work with the whiteboard they are designed for.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Easiteach and related products, which include interactive whiteboards and such peripherals as a <a href=\"/wiki/Dance_pad\" title=\"Dance pad\">dance mat</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> are seen as pivotal to RM, with the <a href=\"/wiki/Investors_Chronicle\" title=\"Investors Chronicle\">Investors Chronicle</a> commenting that its \"<i>near-term growth prospects hinge upon Easiteach, the interactive whiteboards, now installed in over 8,000 UK schools</i>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Easiteach is also widely used outside the UK, with a 2006 estimate of 40,000 installations worldwide.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>RM won four awards at the <a href=\"/wiki/BETT\" title=\"BETT\">British Education and Training and Technology</a> 2005 show, including two for Easyteach Literacy and Easyteach Maths.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Easiteach&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/education/2004/mar/09/elearning.technology12\">The Guardian, eLearning Technology, March 9, 2004</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-7477573/FETC-showcase-the-annual-conference.html\">FETC showcase ... the newest product innovations in educational technology</a> Technological Horizons In Education. January 2008</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tes.co.uk/article.aspx?storycode=2047431\">Content is King</a> C.Drage, <a href=\"/wiki/Times_Educational_Supplement\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Times Educational Supplement\">Times Educational Supplement</a>, 5 November 2004</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.teem.org.uk/2259/content3282.html\">Easiteach Dance Mat Review</a> teem.org.uk, October 2008</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-125624326.html\">RM Results Analysis</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Investors_Chronicle\" title=\"Investors Chronicle\">Investors Chronicle</a> 26 November 2004</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www2.smarttech.com/st/en-US/About+Us/News+Room/SMART+in+the+Media/2006.htm?guid=%7BA9FD9D08-DE95-4C36-8A50-57893787E901%7D\">The Wonders of Interactive Whiteboards</a> Neal Starkman, Technological Horizons In Education, May 2006</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.khaleejtimes.com/DisplayArticle.asp?xfile=data/business/2005/October/business_October151.xml&amp;section=business&amp;col=\">Khaleej Times, A nation of smart schools is becoming a reality in GCC, October 6, 2005</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.rm.com/investors/NewsDetail.asp?cref=IN347274\">RM Website, RM's learning software takes four awards.</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2166\nCached time: 20180918145427\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.028 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.042 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 167/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node co